♫ Something that disappears
without a trace ♫

262
00:19:02,640 --> 00:19:07,170
♫ All I've been doing is thinking ♫

263
00:19:08,610 --> 00:19:14,390
♫ I can't stand that
I keep thinking about it ♫

264
00:19:14,390 --> 00:19:18,380
♫ Unbelievable days of the past ♫

265
00:19:18,380 --> 00:19:21,570
♫ Do what you want ♫

266
00:19:24,200 --> 00:19:28,290
♫ Do what you want ♫

267
00:19:30,960 --> 00:19:36,890
♫ I'm sure everything will get better ♫

268
00:19:36,890 --> 00:19:42,690
♫ The more I get to know you,
you warm my heart ♫

269
00:19:42,690 --> 00:19:48,210
♫ We must never try to stop ♫

270
00:19:48,210 --> 00:19:52,640
♫ I can't erase you from
deep inside my heart ♫

271
00:19:52,640 --> 00:19:54,130
Where are we going?

272
00:19:59,610 --> 00:20:01,590
The nearby park?

273
00:20:02,500 --> 00:20:03,720
Let's go.

274
00:20:20,750 --> 00:20:22,260
Wow, it's so pretty.

275
00:20:23,460 --> 00:20:25,650
Bye! I'm going first.

276
00:20:25,650 --> 00:20:27,110
No!

277
00:20:27,110 --> 00:20:28,510
Go this way.

278
00:20:47,390 --> 00:20:48,380
You're overreacting.

279
00:20:48,380 --> 00:20:50,250
Not overreacting. I'm being careful.

280
00:20:50,250 --> 00:20:51,880
It doesn't hurt to be careful.

281
00:20:51,880 --> 00:20:53,770
"Are you a hypochondriac?"

282
00:20:53,800 --> 00:20:55,900
- That's what you used to say.
- Well...

283
00:20:55,900 --> 00:20:57,400
Back then...

284
00:20:57,400 --> 00:20:59,700
I didn't know you very well.

285
00:20:59,700 --> 00:21:03,840
And when did I ever say it
so argumentatively?

286
00:21:07,450 --> 00:21:09,250
What did the doctor say?

287
00:21:12,450 --> 00:21:13,660
Dr. Cha.

288
00:21:14,990 --> 00:21:16,960
He ran a few tests.

289
00:21:16,960 --> 00:21:20,420
He'll call me when the
detailed test results are out.

290
00:21:20,420 --> 00:21:22,240
You got a comprehensive check-up?

291
00:21:22,240 --> 00:21:23,380
Yes.

292
00:21:23,380 --> 00:21:24,900
In case.

293
00:21:24,900 --> 00:21:26,370
That's all?

294
00:21:26,370 --> 00:21:27,410
Yes.

295
00:21:30,880 --> 00:21:33,100
We should eat these somewhere.

296
00:21:33,100 --> 00:21:34,840
You were craving it.

297
00:21:42,320 --> 00:21:44,880
Did you want to be a doctor
since you were young?

298
00:21:45,660 --> 00:21:46,590
No.

299
00:21:47,400 --> 00:21:49,170
Then what did you want to be?

300
00:21:50,210 --> 00:21:52,250
Well...

301
00:21:52,250 --> 00:21:53,880
A comic book store owner.

302
00:21:55,600 --> 00:21:57,020
Comic book store?

303
00:21:58,140 --> 00:21:59,700
When I was little,

304
00:21:59,700 --> 00:22:02,050
we had an attic in our house.

305
00:22:02,050 --> 00:22:03,360
I see.

306
00:22:03,360 --> 00:22:06,120
I'd stay up there and
read comic books.

307
00:22:06,120 --> 00:22:07,970
I'd feel so relaxed.

308
00:22:07,970 --> 00:22:09,820
As if I was in another world.

309
00:22:11,620 --> 00:22:13,110
It suits you.

310
00:22:14,600 --> 00:22:16,610
What would've suited me?

311
00:22:19,580 --> 00:22:21,530
I can't picture it.

312
00:22:21,530 --> 00:22:23,910
No matter what I picture...

313
00:22:23,910 --> 00:22:27,770
I can't see you without
your doctor's robe.

314
00:22:27,770 --> 00:22:29,080
Is that right?

315
00:22:30,850 --> 00:22:32,740
But why?

316
00:22:33,870 --> 00:22:35,070
Just because.

317
00:22:36,060 --> 00:22:40,550
I did think I may not be able to
work as a doctor someday.

318
00:22:41,610 --> 00:22:43,150
If I quit,

319
00:22:43,150 --> 00:22:45,700
I haven't thought about
what I'll do after.

320
00:22:45,700 --> 00:22:47,320
You'll be quitting?

321
00:22:48,420 --> 00:22:50,140
You're not, right?

322
00:22:50,140 --> 00:22:52,360
I'm just saying.

323
00:22:52,360 --> 00:22:54,210
If something happens...

324
00:22:54,210 --> 00:22:56,270
you must tell me.

325
00:22:56,270 --> 00:22:57,810
Okay?

326
00:22:57,810 --> 00:23:00,160
Yes, I promise.

327
00:23:05,100 --> 00:23:06,420
Dr. Cha...

328
00:23:06,420 --> 00:23:09,160
I don't think you can have
other professions.

329
00:23:09,160 --> 00:23:10,710
Why not?

330
00:23:10,710 --> 00:23:12,900
If you have a regular job,

331
00:23:12,900 --> 00:23:14,930
they'd stiff your pay.

332
00:23:15,980 --> 00:23:18,520
If you run a business, you'd be lied to.

333
00:23:18,520 --> 00:23:21,210
If you do retail, you'd go bankrupt.

334
00:23:21,210 --> 00:23:23,180
Is that a compliment or an insult?

335
00:23:23,180 --> 00:23:24,490
You got me.

336
00:23:32,700 --> 00:23:34,620
Sir, here's the book you wanted.

337
00:23:34,620 --> 00:23:36,590
Okay, thank you.

338
00:23:37,500 --> 00:23:39,080
[ The Categorization of
Medical Care and Bioethics ]

339
00:23:41,510 --> 00:23:44,000
[ Can we achieve happiness by prolonging
our lives with the art of medicine? ]

340
00:23:48,500 --> 00:23:50,200
[ Lee Won Gil ]

341
00:23:51,400 --> 00:23:52,740
[ Lee Won Gil ]

342
00:23:58,460 --> 00:24:00,520
- Yes?
- It's me.

343
00:24:00,520 --> 00:24:02,370
Did you attend the conference?

344
00:24:02,370 --> 00:24:03,270
Yes.

345
00:24:04,210 --> 00:24:05,600
I guess you're out and about.

346
00:24:05,600 --> 00:24:07,170
Well, it's the weekend.

347
00:24:07,170 --> 00:24:09,430
I'm catching up on my cultural activities.

348
00:24:10,620 --> 00:24:12,090
Do you want to join me?

349
00:24:12,090 --> 00:24:14,080
I'm going to look at some paintings.

350
00:24:15,230 --> 00:24:16,700
Paintings?

351
00:24:22,000 --> 00:24:23,300
[ Zinmu Rijund ]

352
00:24:23,300 --> 00:24:26,800
[ Charity Exhibit: Donations for
rare and incurable diseases ]

353
00:24:26,810 --> 00:24:28,650
[ Moonlight Foundation ]

354
00:24:39,080 --> 00:24:41,540
What exhibit is this?

355
00:24:41,540 --> 00:24:44,880
Zinmu Rijund owns a foundation.

356
00:24:44,880 --> 00:24:47,500
A foundation for social
contributions helping patients

357
00:24:47,500 --> 00:24:50,020
with rare, incurable illnesses,
and deemed terminal.

358
00:24:50,020 --> 00:24:51,360
Then...

359
00:24:51,360 --> 00:24:53,820
do they also sponsor that gathering?

360
00:24:55,220 --> 00:24:56,670
It seems that way.

361
00:24:58,840 --> 00:25:01,060
But for me...

362
00:25:02,040 --> 00:25:03,990
why does this painting...

363
00:25:05,160 --> 00:25:07,010
disturb me so?

364
00:25:08,580 --> 00:25:11,570
It's similar to their logo.

365
00:25:11,570 --> 00:25:13,700
And the title...

366
00:25:13,700 --> 00:25:15,230
seems like a code.

367
00:25:15,980 --> 00:25:17,710
[ Hui Won ]

368
00:25:30,600 --> 00:25:32,200
[ The Categorization of
Medical Care and Bioethics ]

369
00:25:43,290 --> 00:25:44,800
The exhibit is closed.

370
00:25:44,800 --> 00:25:45,940
It'll only be a minute.

371
00:25:45,940 --> 00:25:47,690
Can you come back another day?

372
00:25:47,690 --> 00:25:49,660
I left something inside. Sorry.

373
00:25:49,660 --> 00:25:50,730
I'll be right out.

374
00:26:05,300 --> 00:26:06,100
[ Hui Won ]

375
00:26:06,100 --> 00:26:08,500
[ Transcribed at Huiwonjae ]

376
00:26:11,700 --> 00:26:14,100
[ Hui Won ]

377
00:26:14,100 --> 00:26:15,890
[ Transcribed at Huiwonjae ]

378
00:26:15,890 --> 00:26:19,460
[ Lee Won Gil ]

379
00:27:31,730 --> 00:27:34,830
Minister, I guess the
teacher was just here.

380
00:27:34,830 --> 00:27:35,730
Yes, he did.

381
00:27:36,840 --> 00:27:39,630
At last, the results are out.

382
00:27:39,630 --> 00:27:41,270
Is that right?

383
00:27:41,270 --> 00:27:45,490
Humans think that pain is
their lifelong greatest enemy,

384
00:27:45,490 --> 00:27:48,260
and their biggest fear, but...

385
00:27:48,260 --> 00:27:49,930
due to the pain,

386
00:27:49,930 --> 00:27:52,110
we are able to achieve.

387
00:27:52,110 --> 00:27:53,530
Yes.

388
00:27:53,530 --> 00:27:57,730
I discovered it after a torturous pain.

389
00:27:57,730 --> 00:28:00,160
A medication perfect in every way.

390
00:28:00,160 --> 00:28:01,670
Kerubim.

391
00:28:11,480 --> 00:28:12,720
Go on in.

392
00:28:12,720 --> 00:28:14,340
Get home safely.

393
00:28:18,250 --> 00:28:19,910
I'll make an effort.

394
00:28:21,790 --> 00:28:23,460
To not worry you.

395
00:28:28,120 --> 00:28:29,140
Okay.

396
00:28:35,370 --> 00:28:39,470
♫ I can't see no matter how I try ♫

397
00:28:39,470 --> 00:28:45,690
♫ Like a dream which
has ended for me ♫

398
00:28:48,990 --> 00:28:53,220
♫ Deep in the dark shadows ♫

399
00:28:53,220 --> 00:29:00,500
♫ You're still lingering behind me ♫

400
00:29:00,500 --> 00:29:04,690
♫ Even though I'm not able to ♫

401
00:29:04,690 --> 00:29:08,040
♫ Erase away your pain ♫

402
00:29:08,040 --> 00:29:13,660
♫ It's our destiny and
I can't get away ♫

403
00:29:13,660 --> 00:29:20,560
♫ A day full of sorrow and pain ♫

404
00:29:20,560 --> 00:29:27,420
♫ I'm here now, right by your side ♫

405
00:29:27,420 --> 00:29:34,150
♫ Even through every
fading moment ♫

406
00:29:34,150 --> 00:29:40,750
♫ I always trust in you ♫

407
00:29:40,750 --> 00:29:45,640
♫ I trust in you ♫

408
00:29:47,300 --> 00:29:50,000
[ You have a new message ]

409
00:29:50,010 --> 00:29:52,010
Dr. Kang Shi Young, please join us.

410
00:29:56,500 --> 00:29:58,200
[ Hansae Wish Club ]

411
00:29:58,760 --> 00:30:00,880
"Hansae Wish Club."

412
00:30:24,730 --> 00:30:26,790
We'll be doing this?

413
00:30:29,850 --> 00:30:32,520
We want to do something like this.

414
00:30:32,520 --> 00:30:34,420
If the patient is willing.

415
00:30:34,420 --> 00:30:36,490
I'm so thankful, but...

416
00:30:36,490 --> 00:30:38,770
my sister may not want anything.

417
00:30:38,770 --> 00:30:40,820
She has lost her will.

418
00:30:40,820 --> 00:30:42,610
Even trivial things are okay.

419
00:30:42,610 --> 00:30:46,070
As a matter of fact, let us know
if she's craving any food.

420
00:30:46,070 --> 00:30:49,070
Anything is fine. Please ask her for us.

421
00:30:49,070 --> 00:30:53,220
She told me not to visit
and won't even see me.

422
00:30:54,840 --> 00:30:58,030
Dr. Kang, could you please ask her?

423
00:30:59,120 --> 00:31:00,340
Me?

424
00:31:00,340 --> 00:31:02,580
True. You're her doctor.

425
00:31:02,580 --> 00:31:04,420
Go on in.

426
00:31:04,420 --> 00:31:06,970
- Please...
- Go ahead.

427
00:31:06,970 --> 00:31:11,410
♫ Until she calls you ♫

428
00:31:18,100 --> 00:31:22,490
♫ It won't be wrong ♫

429
00:31:24,210 --> 00:31:27,033
♫ For you to love again ♫
